class.description:
A type to define enums as bitfield. Certain warnings that would normally be raised when exporting or returning enums will automatically get ignored. When exporting this type, it will automatically obtain [constant PROPERTY_HINT_FLAGS] and [constant PROPERTY_USAGE_CLASS_IS_BITFIELD], similar to [annotation @GDScript.@export_flags].
When passed around, this type behaves like a regular integer. This type supports being nested into other collection types.
[b]Note:[/b] This type cannot be inferred, it has to be specified.
[b]Note:[/b] Languages other than GDScript may define bitfields in their own way. For example, in C#, enums are marked with the [code][Flags][/code] attribute, which has the same effect.
Example:
[codeblock]
enum Direction {
	LEFT = 1,
	RIGHT = 2,
	UP = 4,
	DOWN = 8,
}

# Usage:
@export var direction: BitField[Direction]
@export var regular_enum: Direction # Raises ENUM_VARIABLE_WITHOUT_DEFAULT.

# Nesting is supported:
@export var array: Array[BitField[Direction]]
@export var dict: Dictionary[BitField[Direction], BitField[Direction]]

func return_regular_enum() -> Direction:
	return Direction.LEFT | Direction.RIGHT # Raises INT_AS_ENUM_WITHOUT_CAST and INT_AS_ENUM_WITHOUT_MATCH.

func return_bitfield() -> BitField[Direction]:
	return Direction.LEFT | Direction.RIGHT # No warnings.
[/codeblock]
